==Scots==

===Etymology===
From the word [[odios]].

===Adjective===
'''ojis'''

# [[great]]
#: ''"That's ojis"'' (that's great)
#: ''"He's an ojis eejit"'' (he's a great fool)

===Usage Notes===
Used in dialects of Scots/English spoken in [[Northern Ireland]].

'''Dialects Affected:'''
*Ulster Scots (Ullans)
*Hiberno-English
*Mid-Ulster English